attributes.gcd: Refers to the date on which the account is closed. Account can be an active or closed, this column will remain blank till account is active. Accounts can be closed upon maturity, transfer or death of a customer.

Refers to the account manager is an employee who is responsible for the day to day management of accounts of a particular customer. The account manager is a point of contact, and provides customer support, up selling, technical assistance and general relationship management. An account manager may be in charge of a number of smaller accounts, or may focus on a few larger accounts. This column Refers to the account manager code or the unique employee identifier of the manager assigned by the financial institution. Management Dimension is the equivalent dimension table for this column.

Refers to the date on which the account was opened in the financial institution. This is the system date on which the financial institution opens the account. It may or may not be equal to effective date.

Refers to the unique identifier of the account or contract held by the customer. Account number is defined as numbers, letters or alphanumeric code assigned to every significant customer, supplier and lender for ease of reference in accounting records of the financial institution.
Refers to the channel through which customer was acquired.

Refers to the annual income of the applicant or applicant or party or customer. Annual income is the total amount of income earned annually. Gross annual income represents the amount of money a person earns in one year from all sources before annual taxes are evaluated.
Refers to the age of the applicant.
Refers to the bank account number of the applicant.
Refers to the bank address of the applicant.
Refers to the bank name of the applicant.
Refers to the cell phone number of the applicant.
Refers to the applicant education.
Refers to the phone number of employer of the applicant.
Refers to the estimated annual revenue of applicants.
Refers to the first name of applicant.
Refers to the unique gender code of the applicant. Reference dimensional table is Gender dimension.
Refers to the home ownership status of the applicant.
Refers to the home phone number of the applicant.
Refers to the household income of the applicant or co applicant.
Refers to the applicant identifier.
Refers to the industry segment to which the applicant belongs.
Refers to the last name of the applicant.
Refers to the unique identifier of the marital status as married, unmarried or other.
Refers to the middle name of the applicant.
Refers to the office phone number of the applicant.
Refers to the profession of the party.
Refers to the other phone number of the applicant.
Refers to the preferred language of the applicant. Expected values are FR, NL, DE, etc.

Refers to the pre sales value for property associated with the loan. The presales are mostly in case where loan is taken for property that is being constructed or developed for further sale for residential or commercial purposes.
Refers to the value of the property.
Refers to the first line of the address component of this residential address.
Refers to the third line of the address component of this residential address.
Refers to the second line of the address component of this residential address.
Refers to the zip code of residence of the applicant.
Refers to the status of the applicant.
Refers to the unique identifier assigned to the agent.
Flag indicates if the application is approved. List of values are Y, N.
Refers to the date when Application is closed. No further changes may occur to the Application after this date.

attributes.logicalName: Application Contact Point Verification End Date
attributes.gcd: Refers to the date on which the contact point verification ends.

attributes.logicalName: Application Contact Point Verification Start Date
attributes.gcd: Refers to the date on which the contact point verification has started.
Indicates the score was used for decision process using score indicator.
Refers to the date on which the decision is taken on an application.
Refers to the application decision codes like pending, referred, cancelled and so on.
Indicates if the documents have been completed for the application.
Refers to the online application, the stage or the step during which the application process is stopped or terminated.

attributes.logicalName: Application Duration Of Complete Contact Point Verification
attributes.gcd: Refers to the time taken to complete contact point verification.

attributes.logicalName: Application Duration Of Complete Internal Defaulter List Search
attributes.gcd: Refers to the time taken to complete internal defaulter list search.

attributes.logicalName: Application Duration Of Complete Negative List Search
attributes.gcd: Refers to the time taken to complete negative list search.

attributes.logicalName: Application Duration Of Complete Pre Screening
attributes.gcd: Refers to the time taken to complete pre screening process.

attributes.logicalName: Application Duration Of Complete Referral Verification
attributes.gcd: Refers to the time taken to complete referral verification.

attributes.logicalName: Application Duration Of Complete Residence Search
attributes.gcd: Refers to the time taken to complete the residence search.
Indicates if the application is a likely fraud application.
Refers to the application group identifier that was submitted by the customer that formed the basis for the contract.
Indicates applications referred in prior months.

attributes.logicalName: Application Internal Defaulter List Search End Date
attributes.gcd: Refers to the date on which the internal defaulter list search ends.

attributes.logicalName: Application Internal Defaulter List Search Start Date
attributes.gcd: Refers to the date on which the internal defaulter list search has started.
Refers to the date on which the last status was updated for the document associated to an application.

attributes.logicalName: Application Low And Moderate Income Tracts Flag
attributes.gcd: Flag indicates the low and moderate income tracts applications. List of values are Y, N.

attributes.logicalName: Application Negative List Search End Date
attributes.gcd: Refers to the date on which the negative list search ends.

attributes.logicalName: Application Negative List Search Start Date
attributes.gcd: Refers to the date on which the negative list search has started.
Indicates the score was not used for decision process using non score exclusion indicator.

Refers to the application number that was filled by the customer that formed the basis for the contract. Application is a document that provides the essential financial and other information about the borrower on which the lender bases the decision to lend.
Refers to the field captures data in case of application being originated to websites like amazon, ndtv, yahoo and Rediff, etc.
Refers to the parent card number in case application being requested for add on or supplementary card.
Refers to the date on which the positive search ends.
Refers to the date on which the positive search has started.
Refers to the application process string formulated depending upon the completion of application processing stages.
Refers to the unique identifier of the promotion code for the campaign.
Refers to the unique identifier of the application Purpose.
Refers to the date on which the application is received.
Refers to the unique identifier of the referral code.
Refers to the date on which the referral verification ends.
Refers to the date on which the referral verification has started.
Refers to the reason for rejection of the application such as incomplete documents, data mismatch, credit history etc.
Refers to the amount requested by the applicant.
Refers to the date on which the residence verification ends.
Refers to the date on which the residence verification has started.

Refers to the unique sequence number for an application. Sequence number is required to store multiple products in an application and different status associated with each product like approved, reject etc.
Refers to the unique identifier of the application status as approved, rejected etc.
Indicates the supplementary card application.
Refers to the unique identifier of the terminal.

attributes.logicalName: Application Terms And Conditions Acceptance Date
attributes.gcd: Refers to the date when Terms and Conditions associated with the Application is accepted by the Customers.

attributes.logicalName: Application Terms And Conditions Offer Date
attributes.gcd: Refers to the date when Terms and Conditions associated with the Application is offered to the Customers.
Refers to the type of the application like fresh, existing and enhancement.
Refers to the date on which the application is verified.

Refers to the amount approved for the loan or line. This may differ from the actual contract amount or loan amount. Usually approved amount is the maximum exposure, the financial institution is willing to take on a contract.
Refers to the date as on which the snapshot of source data extracted for processing.

Flag indicates whether bank has documentation of all the relevant criteria considered for the ability of borrower to repay. This includes documentation pertaining to Existing loans of borrower, tenancy profile relative to loan maturity of commercial property, impact of interest rates etc. List of values are Y, N. A value of Y indicates that the bank has all the appropriate documentation capturing the ability of borrower to repay. A value of N will indicate that not all the required documentation are available with the bank. Null will be treated as N.

Refers to the branch code. A branch, banking center or financial center is a retail location where a financial institution offers a wide array of face to face and automated services to its customers. This column Refers to the unique branch code assigned by the financial institution. A branch may specialize to offer certain type of products to customers. Branch needs approval from the regulators.

Flag to indicate whether the application i.e the potential loan is bulk insurable. Bulk insurance covers the scenarios where the lending institution purchases insurance at a portfolio level where each portfolio consists of multiple accounts. The list of values are Y and N.

Refers to the unique identifier of the campaign under which the account was acquired. Campaign is defined as Specific activities designed to promote a product, service or business. A marketing campaign is a coordinated series of steps that can include promotion of a product through different mediums like television, radio, print, online using a variety of different types of advertisements. The campaign doesn't have to rely solely on advertising, and can also include demonstrations, word of mouth and other interactive techniques. Campaigns are created or started by financial institutions to promote sales, improve visibility of the brand or product and create opportunities for addon sales and cross selling.

Refers to the cashback amount advanced to the customer at the time of fund disbursement. This amount is typically negotiated with the customer at the time of mortgage approval. This amount is usually calculated as a percentage of the funded amount depending on the ongoing promotional offer at the time of approval.
Refers to the unique city code of this location.
Refers to the unique identifier of the credit centre code.
Refers to the unique identifier of the credit officer processing the application. The credit officer evaluates the credit worthiness by assessing the ability and the willingness of the borrower.
Refers to the credit or FICO score of application.

Refers to the source system from where data is extracted. Data can be sourced from multiple sources, this column will Refers to the source code from where the data is extracted for this extraction date.

Refers to alphanumeric code that identifies the primary down payment source for the loan application. Example, OWN FUNDS, BORROWED FUNDS, SWEAT EQUITY, GIFT, ETC. Associated dimension table for this attribute is Down Payment Source Dimension i.e. sourced dimension which can be populated using master table Stage Down Payment Source Master.
Flag indicates the insurance if the party has health insurance. List of values are Y, N.

ISO currency codes is a standard published by the International Organization for Standardization 4217, which delineates currency designators and country codes, alpha and numeric. This column will capture the standardized currency code. Currency dimension is the equivalent dimension table for this column.
Refers to the ISO State code of the Address. International Organization for Standardization, ISO, and defines codes for each state.

Refers to the insurance Auto License Reinstatement Date of party. In the event a license of person was suspended or revoked, this will be the date most recently reinstated. If a license of person is currently suspended, this date should not be valued.
Flag indicates the Insurance Auto License Suspended Flag. List of values are Y, N.

attributes.logicalName: Insurance Auto Violation Points As Of Date
attributes.gcd: Refers to the insurance Auto Violation Points As Of Date reflecting points information.
Refers to the insurance Birth weight of the person, stored in grams. In the case of juvenile insured that was born premature, the birth weight is frequently needed.

Flag indicates the insurance if the party is expected a child in the near future. List of values are Y, N. A Dependent Child is Expected, Y indicates a person is expecting a child that may be considered eligible for additional coverage. For example, this indicator may be true if the insured were pregnant or the wife of insured were pregnant. N indicates a person is NOT expecting a child that may be considered eligible for additional coverage.

attributes.logicalName: Insurance Currently Lives In Nursing Home Flag
attributes.gcd: Flag indicates the insurance if the party currently lives in a nursing home. List of values are Y, N.
Refers to the insurance Disability of party Effective End Date.
Refers to the insurance Disability of party Effective Start Date.
Flag indicates the insurance if the party has an existing insurance. List of values are Y, N.

Flag indicates the insurance Insurance Funding Disclosure Flag. List of values are Y, N. On Risk, FundingDisclosureInd is where the CLIENT indicates replacement funding. Use FundingDisclosureInd on Application Info to specify the AGENT is indicating the Client is using funds from an existing contract.

Flag indicates the insurance if the party knows his Family History. An indicator used to specify if the family history is known. For instance, this would be used to indicate if a person was adopted and did not know their family history. List of values are Y, N. If Y, family history is known and if N, is not known.
Refers to the Insurance last hospitalized date.
Refers to the insurance Last Physician Visited.

attributes.logicalName: Insurance Last Risk Information Updated Date
attributes.gcd: Refers to the Insurance Last Risk Information Updated Date, this is the last date that the overall Risk information was updated.

Flag indicates the Insurance Medical Assistance Flag. If the party need any assistance due to medical condition. Y indicates a person requires assistance for daily living chores. N indicates a person does NOT require assistance for daily living chores. List of values are Y, N.
Refers to the insurance Number of Brothers Dead of the party.
Refers to the insurance Number of Brothers Living of the party.
Refers to the insurance Number of Sisters Dead of the party.
Refers to the insurance Number of Sisters Living of the party.
Flag indicates the insurance permanent disabled flag. List of values are Y, N. Y indicates that the person is permanently disabled and confined to a wheelchair, N indicates no.
Flag indicates the insurance if the party is Receiving any Disability Benefits. List of values are Y, N.

Flag indicates the insurance if the party has any recent health change. List of values are Y, N. Recent Health Changed Indicator, TRUE indicates a person reported a recent change in health. FALSE indicates a person has NOT reported a recent change in health. Specific illness, time period and exact wording vary by jurisdiction.

Flag indicates the insurance rejected flag . List of values are Y, N. List of values are Y indicates a person has been rejected for life, health, disability or long term care insurance. N indicates they have NOT been rejected for life, health, disability or long term care insurance.
Flag indicates the insurance if the party was hospitalized for any serious illness. List of values are Y, N.
Refers to the insurance special term end last date, date the last contract was issued with special terms.

Flag indicates the insurance if the party is a user of tobacco or not. List of values are Y, N. Y indicates the party has used in the past or is currently using tobacco or any other product that contained nicotine. N indicates the party has never used tobacco or any other product that contained nicotine.

attributes.logicalName: Insurance Total Accidental Death Benefit Inforce
attributes.gcd: Refers to the Insurance Total Accidental Death Benefit Inforce Amount. An amount indicating the total dollar amount of accidental death benefit insurance that is in force for the individual.

attributes.logicalName: Insurance Total Disability Income Inforce Amount
attributes.gcd: Refers to the insurance Total Disability Income Inforce.
Refers to the Insurance Total Inforce Amount. Sum of Insurance Total Inforce Personal Amount plus Insurance Total Inforce Business Amount.

attributes.logicalName: Insurance Total Inforce And Applied Amount
attributes.gcd: Refers to the Total Amount Inforce And Applied Insurance. Total Inforce and Applied Insurance, To be used when the Total amount of In force and Applied for Insurance as distinct amounts are unknown. If the amount of each is known separately, use the more granular Total Inforce Ins and Total Applied ForIns properties in addition to this property.

Refers to the insurance Total Amount Business Inforce. On Risk, the sum of Total Personal Inforce Insurance and Total Business Inforce Insurance should equal Total Inforce Insurance when all elements are present.

Refers to the insurance Total Amount Personal Inforce. On Risk, the sum of Total Amount Personal Inforce Insurance and Total Business Inforce Insurance should equal Total Inforce Insurance when all elements are present.
Refers to the insurance Total Amount of Pending Reinstatement, To be used to represent the total face amount of Insurance that is pending reinstatement.

attributes.logicalName: Insurance Treatment In Absence Of Medical Condition Flag
attributes.gcd: Flag indicates the insurance if the party has undergone any treatments without any medical conditions. List of values are Y, N. Y is yes, indicates that Medical Treatments are attached without a medical condition, N is no, do NOT look for Medical treatment unless they are attached to a Medical Condition.

attributes.logicalName: Insurance Under Special Term Company Name
attributes.gcd: Refers to the insurance under Special Term Company Name.

Flag indicates the insurance if the policy of party is taken up by the insurance company on any of the special terms. Special Terms Flag, Y indicates the person has previously been issued insurance with special terms. N indicates the person has not previously been issued insurance with special terms. Special terms means rated or Exclusion, or both. List of values are Y, N.
Refers to the insurance under special term reason. The reason why the policy was issued at a special term. Description of the special terms of most recently affected policy.

Refers to the Insurance Underwriting Issue sub type for the policy. this is to provide additional detail about the type of underwriting that was applied to the coverage, Sample values are OTHER is other, UNKNOWN is unknown, FULLMED is Full Medical, NONMED is Non Medical, PARAMED is Paramedical.

Refers to the Insurance Underwriting Issue type for the policy. For example, Full Underwriting, Mass Underwriting, Reduced Underwriting, Simplified Underwriting, etc., sample values are OTHER is other, UNKNOWN is unknown, AVIATION is Aviation, PERCOVERAGE is Blended Policy has Underwritten and Guaranteed Issue coverages. Only applies at Policy Level, CONVERTED is Conversion No underwriting done, NONCNTRCTCONVERT is Conversion Non contractual, EXPRESS is Express Underwriting, FIELDISSUE is Field Issue, FINANCIALUNDERWRITTEN is Financial Underwriting, FULL is Full Underwriting, GUAR is Guaranteed Issue, MASSUNDERWRITING is Mass Underwriting, REDUCED UNDERWRITING is Reduced Underwriting, SIMP is Simplified Underwriting.

Refers to the Weight Change Reason. On Risk, Weight Change Reason may be used on its own or in conjunction with Weight Change Response Type to document the reasons and other details relating to a change in weight that is not tied to a documented medical condition. Weight changes associated with a documented medical condition including pregnancy should be specified using the Weight Change property under Medical Condition.

Refers to the Weight Change Response Type. On Risk, additional details relating to an affirmative response that does not relate to a documented medical condition may be modeled using the Weight Change Reason property also under Risk. Weight changes associated with a documented medical condition including pregnancy should be specified using the Weight Change property under Medical Condition. Sample values are POS as Applies, NEG as Does not apply, Other, unknown, UNKNOWN as Stated as Not Known.
Refers to the type of interest rate paid on this transaction., For instance Fixed Or Floating.

Flag to indicate if the account is jointly held by two or more individuals which means if the value is updated as Y the account is held by two or more people and if the value is updated as N the account is held by single entity.
Refers to the entity code of the legal entity to which the account will be attributed in the general ledger.

Refers to line of business, LOB, is a functional unit that offers the products to the customer by the financial entity. Example: Corporate Finance, Trade Services, Private Wealth Management, Treasury Services, Retail Banking, Cards services etc. Refers to the unique code of the line of business applicable to the respective product.
Refers to the tenor for the loan.
Refers to the unique location code. Location code is defined as the code which will represent the address of the property from zip code onwards like which city, country etc.

Refers to the contractual date on which the principal balance is expected to fully amortize and the balance payable would be nil. This is applicable for term loan products but not for revolving credit or overdraft type of account. In case of insurance policy, for some whole life insurance products the maturity date is aligned to maximum attained age and the policy is payable upon the earlier of the maturity date or the death of the insured. In case of Term Life insurance policies the maturity date is determined as policy issue date plus Term of the contract. In case of an annuity it is the date from which the annuitant has chosen to take the payouts.

Refers to the mode of payment. The common modes of payment are Cash, Cheque, Debit card, Credit card, Electronic Fund Transfer etc. 
The payment instruction is governed under negotiable instruments act, which is referred to under article 3 and 4 of Uniform Commercial Code. This does not apply to cash.
Refers to the number of dependents on the party.

attributes.logicalName: Number Of Other Cards Held By Applicant
attributes.gcd: Refers to the number of other cards held by the applicant if the application is for cards related accounts.
Refers to the number of years that the applicant has been employed.

Refers to the line one of address like apartment or house number, apartment name, street, cross, road etc. where the party is residing. More important fields like city, state are captured in separate fields.

Refers to the line three of address like apartment or house number, apartment name, street, cross, road etc. where the party is residing. More important fields like city, state are captured in separate fields.
Refers to the address line 2 of the party or customer office address details.
Refers to the original debt servicing ratio.
Refers to the original loan rate.
Flag indicates whether the property is occupied by the owner or not. List of values are Y, N.

Refers to the unique identifier of product bundle code. Bundling is a marketing strategy that joins products or services together in order to sell them as a single combined unit. Bundling allows the convenient purchase of several products and or services from the same financial institution. The products and services are usually related, but they can also consist of dissimilar products which appeal to one group of customers. For example Credit card product is bundled with savings account product or loan product is bundled with a CASA account. There are certain interest cost advantages that are available as part of product bundle, should the customer close a product which is part of the bundle, the financial institution could review the advantage provided to other accounts as part of the bundle.

Refers to the security for which this order has been placed. Expected values are EQT  Equity, FI  Fixed Income, CFI  Corporate Fixed Income, OPT  Option, FUT  Future, FX  Foreign Exchange, MF  Mutual Fund, COM  Commodity, ETF  Exchange Traded Fund, MM  Money Market, PRE  Preferred, CONV  Convertible, SWAP Swap, OTH  Other, INF  Insurance Fund.
Refers to the unique code assigned to each of the Products offered by the Bank.

Refers to the country code where the property is located. There are several popular country codes as part of ISO 3166 standard published by the International Organization for Standardization. ISO 3166 defines codes for the names of countries, dependent territories, special areas of geographical interest and their principal subdivisions.
Refers to the property type code associated with given account. Property Dimension is the equivalent dimension table for this column.
Refers to the unique identifier of the prospect.

Refers to the standard rate set by the regulators that mortgages which is usually insured mortgages must adhere to. This is used in stress testing scenarios. Example, all insured mortgages, regardless of term, fixed or variable interest rates bearing, are expected to qualify for the greater of the contract rate or the prevalent Bank of Canada benchmark rate. Such greater rate is the qualifying rate.
Refers to the record creation date. It has been added to all catalog entities to enable partitioning and archival.
Refers to the Referral fees or compensation received from a mortgage lender for referring a customer.

Refers to the geographical grouping of the market based on certain common characteristics like language, ethnicity, country, continent, city and state. The region can vary based on the definition of market. Global market vs local market can have different definition of region.
Refers to the run identifier for a set of Records participating in the particular Run with the Run Execution identifier. This is a combination of Run Main Identifier and Run Execution Identifier.

Refers to the unique identifier of the sales representative associated with the account. A product offering of a bank is usually sold via multiple channels. Sales representatives are usually employed to sell certain types of products like insurance policies, mutual funds etc. DIM_SALES_REPRESENTATIVE is the equivalent dimension table for this column.
